\fs48 \ul Misconceptions\ulnone \

\fs28 "But the Pear eLicense requires you to sell your soul!"\

\f1\i\b No, it does not. The Pear eLicense, no matter what, does not require one to sell their soul to any party in any way.\

\f0\i0\b0 "Pear doesn't care about innovation, they care about your money and data!"\

\f1\i\b This is very false. We at Pear indeed care about innovation, and we at Pear have had pastaOS, by itself, be free and always be free (in terms of price), and we NEVER collect any data that isn't needed by Pear. However, the services one uses collect data by themselves if owned by a third-party, so be wary of that.
